The paper deals with the analysis of photoluminescence wafer images using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of densely connected convolutional blocks and atrous spatial pyramid pooling modules suggests a focus on deep learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of working with small datasets, which is a common issue in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of photoluminescence imaging suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
